{"id": "ChIJvwDoN82Rj4ARcMDyt30Fg9U", "rating": 4.3, "userRatingCount": 90, "displayName": {"text": "Tang Jip", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJvwDoN82Rj4ARcMDyt30Fg9U/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xkS1VsUmhhR3BZYUU5YVZIVldkR3hVTTBoZlpYYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "We discovered Tang Jip for the first time right before Mother’s Day and chose it for our Mother’s Day dinner. Unfortunately, by the time we arrived, they were already out of one of our favorite dishes, the spicy pork bulgogi, and they also would not refill the banchan. For our family, those are pretty essential parts of the Korean dining experience, so it was disappointing and made it hard to fully judge the restaurant fairly.\n\nThat said, the dishes we did get were very good. The restaurant stayed extremely busy the entire night with a long line out the door, but they did a good job turning tables quickly and getting people seated efficiently.\n\nThe service felt a little inconsistent. It sometimes took a while to get assistance, and we often had to ask more than once for things we needed. It may have been because of the holiday rush, but it still impacted the experience. I also think it was a missed opportunity to have ordering kiosks at the table without the ability to pay through them, and table buzzers like many other Korean restaurants would have made getting service much easier.\n\nOverall, we would definitely go back because the food itself was good, but probably not on a major holiday like Mother’s Day.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "We discovered Tang Jip for the first time right before Mother’s Day and chose it for our Mother’s Day dinner. Unfortunately, by the time we arrived, they were already out of one of our favorite dishes, the spicy pork bulgogi, and they also would not refill the banchan. For our family, those are pretty essential parts of the Korean dining experience, so it was disappointing and made it hard to fully judge the restaurant fairly.\n\nThat said, the dishes we did get were very good. The restaurant stayed extremely busy the entire night with a long line out the door, but they did a good job turning tables quickly and getting people seated efficiently.\n\nThe service felt a little inconsistent. It sometimes took a while to get assistance, and we often had to ask more than once for things we needed. It may have been because of the holiday rush, but it still impacted the experience. I also think it was a missed opportunity to have ordering kiosks at the table without the ability to pay through them, and table buzzers like many other Korean restaurants would have made getting service much easier.\n\nOverall, we would definitely go back because the food itself was good, but probably not on a major holiday like Mother’s Day.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Alyx Lofton (Chabot Business Solutions)", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112427430283622348184/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWgqLphCwS5oU6KAVUyR_E4AUJzt2Vh9_moRkdE-1wPNnWwaK13=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-14T18:47:58.901039583Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xkS1VsUmhhR3BZYUU5YVZIVldkR3hVTTBoZlpYYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xkS1VsUmhhR3BZYUU5YVZIVldkR3hVTTBoZlpYYxAB!2m1!1s0x808f91cd37e800bf:0xd583057db7f2c070"}, {"name": "places/ChIJvwDoN82Rj4ARcMDyt30Fg9U/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2w5MGVGTjJWR053UnpBdExXZHRZM0JLTFhOd1pIYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "I really enjoyed the food at Tang Jip overall. The flavors are solid and definitely hit the spot for Korean cuisine lovers.\n\nOne highlight for me was the raw crab—they offer both soy sauce and spicy red sauce versions, which is great. Personally, I prefer the spicy red sauce over the soy sauce one; it had more depth and bold flavor and felt more satisfying.\n\nThe beef ribs were also very good—tender and flavorful—but I do think they’re a bit pricey for the portion.\n\nCustomer service was friendly and polite, which I appreciated. However, service was pretty slow when it came to getting things we asked for, so expect a bit of waiting.\n\nOverall, delicious food and good vibes, just be prepared for slower service and higher prices on some dishes. Would still come back, especially for the spicy raw crab 😋", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "I really enjoyed the food at Tang Jip overall. The flavors are solid and definitely hit the spot for Korean cuisine lovers.\n\nOne highlight for me was the raw crab—they offer both soy sauce and spicy red sauce versions, which is great. Personally, I prefer the spicy red sauce over the soy sauce one; it had more depth and bold flavor and felt more satisfying.\n\nThe beef ribs were also very good—tender and flavorful—but I do think they’re a bit pricey for the portion.\n\nCustomer service was friendly and polite, which I appreciated. However, service was pretty slow when it came to getting things we asked for, so expect a bit of waiting.\n\nOverall, delicious food and good vibes, just be prepared for slower service and higher prices on some dishes. Would still come back, especially for the spicy raw crab 😋", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "EZ life", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113047589052030970186/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8WEG154ziJIyvzwQIULPfMcJh98D7qpEMXlAON93g2Zw0RRU=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5"}, "publishTime": "2026-02-11T02:00:43.684677930Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2w5MGVGTjJWR053UnpBdExXZHRZM0JLTFhOd1pIYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2w5MGVGTjJWR053UnpBdExXZHRZM0JLTFhOd1pIYxAB!2m1!1s0x808f91cd37e800bf:0xd583057db7f2c070"}, {"name": "places/ChIJvwDoN82Rj4ARcMDyt30Fg9U/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pWQlFWSmFUWEo0UTBKMlFXNXhVV1p2VlZndE5XYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "The food is delicious! Especially their kimchi! It is not sour at all, which is my favorite! I did buy extra container of it when I went home. The tofu stew in the combo is sooooo tiny. The servers are very friendly, atmosphere is great! Will come back again before leaving Bay Area!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "The food is delicious! Especially their kimchi! It is not sour at all, which is my favorite! I did buy extra container of it when I went home. The tofu stew in the combo is sooooo tiny. The servers are very friendly, atmosphere is great! Will come back again before leaving Bay Area!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "WeiWei", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102354243702646515293/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUFZ6NVWpN1WqSfklGKpLXfQHOA4J-6ctNG_JQ3dsZA599PKLg=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba3"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-07T02:05:39.124566288Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pWQlFWSmFUWEo0UTBKMlFXNXhVV1p2VlZndE5XYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pWQlFWSmFUWEo0UTBKMlFXNXhVV1p2VlZndE5XYxAB!2m1!1s0x808f91cd37e800bf:0xd583057db7f2c070"}, {"name": "places/ChIJvwDoN82Rj4ARcMDyt30Fg9U/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25sRlFXZElTMU51ZDFsalRVTkxlVXhZZWtKU2JsRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "rating": 4, "text": {"text": "Went there for Christmas eve dinner, did not want to over order.  Got  chicken katsu n tofu soup combo. Was perfect quality for 3 person. Food is delicious, tastes is more authentic than some other Korean restaurant. price is reasonable. Will come back again", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Went there for Christmas eve dinner, did not want to over order.  Got  chicken katsu n tofu soup combo. Was perfect quality for 3 person. Food is delicious, tastes is more authentic than some other Korean restaurant. price is reasonable. Will come back again", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Steve Thai", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102374145168440516928/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLvBCT25xeGFUnnIOakyAqgqcP4RL0Pm_tjj9po8NvIcAhRXA=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2025-12-28T19:29:40.635568291Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25sRlFXZElTMU51ZDFsalRVTkxlVXhZZWtKU2JsRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25sRlFXZElTMU51ZDFsalRVTkxlVXhZZWtKU2JsRRAB!2m1!1s0x808f91cd37e800bf:0xd583057db7f2c070"}, {"name": "places/ChIJvwDoN82Rj4ARcMDyt30Fg9U/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25oSU0wOWFOVmxtVFVGWlIzbDVhMFZyWW01emJWRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "8 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Food was great! Spice level of the chicken was perfect and the beef was very tender. Server kindly brought us an extra serving of each banchan after requesting. The kimchi could marinate a little longer, but overall everything was very flavorful! We arrived around 3pm on a Monday there was plenty of open seating.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Food was great! Spice level of the chicken was perfect and the beef was very tender. Server kindly brought us an extra serving of each banchan after requesting. The kimchi could marinate a little longer, but overall everything was very flavorful! We arrived around 3pm on